cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.AR 

This paper focuses on structured sparse training of convolutional neural networks (CNNs) for image classification tasks. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.CV (Computer Vision) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also discusses the impact of pruning on the network's performance, which falls under the category of cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the paper discusses the potential hardware acceleration of the proposed method, which could fall under the category of cs.AR (Hardware Architecture).
